    "A discussion with a teacher would include that competence but also, to different extents, some pressure to position oneself as competent in front of the teaching staff, whereas it is possible to bombard an LLM with questions without worrying about how the LLM is perceiving one as a student.",
    "It may be argued that there is still pressure to perform as competent in front of one's teammates, so an individual assignment may result in even more comfort when interacting with the LLM in this manner.The assignment sparked discussions and reflections -supported by the LLM-on critical thinking and action, including the equivalent for awareness and responsibility.",
    "Thus, it covered well an introduction to the ethical process by Lennerfors et al. [25].As the students point out, LLMs can provide different answers to the same (or similar) prompt due to, e.g., ambiguity in the text, sensitivity to the wording, and the randomness used during the text generation process [45].",
